obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (40208)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40208&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Land Holdings`
  line `(Ceiling) Act, 1960.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi, but shall not apply to--`
  line
  line `(a) the areas which, immediately before the 1st day of November, 1956, were included in a`
  line `municipality or in a notified area under the provisions of the Punjab Municipal Act, 1911(Punjab Act`
  line `3 of 1911), or in a cantonment under the provisions of the Cantonments Act, 1924 (2 of 1924);`
  line
  line `(b) the areas ^1[owned and held by the Central Government or any State Governmentort ] any local`
  line `authority; ^2***`
  line
  line `^3[(bb) the areas owned and held by any corporation owned or controlled by the Central`
  line Government;]
  line
  line `^4[(c) the areas acquired under any law relating to the acquisition of land for a public purpose;`
  line
  line `(d) the areas held and occupied, on the appointed day, for the purpose of a goshala or for the`
  line `purpose of breeding, or feeding, or both, of horses, and, in either case, declared as such in the`
  line `prescribed manner by the Chief Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that, no declaration under this clause shall be made by the Chief Commissioner in`
  line `respect of an area held and occupied for the purpose of a goshala unless the goshala has been`
  line `established for a charitable purpose without any motive for profit and registered as a society under the`
  line `Societies Registration Act, 1860 (21 of 1860) and the entire income from such area is utilised for the`
  line `purpose of the goshala:`
  line
  line `Provided further that, when any area or any part thereof ceases to be held and occupied for the`
  line `purpose referred to in this clause any declaration made under this clause, shall cease to have effect`
  line `either in whole or in part, as the case may be, and the provisions of this Act shall apply to the whole`
  line `or part of such area accordingly; and`
  line
  line `(e) the areas owned and held by any agricultural co-operative land mortgage bank, any State or`
  line `Central Co-operative Bank or any other bank.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this clause, "bank" means a banking company as defined in`
  line `section 5 of the Banking Regulation Act, 1949 (10 of 1949) and includes the State Bank of India`
  line `constituted under the State Bank of India Act, 1955 (23 of 1955), a subsidiary bank as defined in the`
  line `State Bank of India (Subsidiary Banks) Act, 1959 (38 of 1959), a corresponding new bank as defined`
  line `in the Banking Companies (Acquisition and Transfer of Undertakings) Act, 1970 (5 of 1970) and the`
  line `Agricultural Refinance Corporation established under the Agricultural Refinance Corporation Act,`
  line `1963 (10 of 1963)].`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date as the Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 2, for "owned by the Central Government" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. The word "and" omitted by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 2,ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 2, ibid. for clause (c) (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (40209)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definition.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40209&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `^1[(a) "appointed day" means the 24th day of January, 1971;]`
  line
  line `^2[(aa)] "ceiling limit", in relation to land, means the limit fixed under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "Chief Commissioner" means the Chief Commissioner of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(c) "competent authority" means any person or authority authorised by the Chief Commissioner`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette to perform the functions of the competent authority under this`
  line `Act for such area as may be specified in the notification;`
  line
  line `^3[(d) "family", in relation to a person, means the person, the wife or husband, as the case may be,`
  line `and the minor sons and unmarried minor daughters of such person;]`
  line
  line `(e) "minor" means a person who is deemed not to have attained majority under the Indian`
  line `Majority Act, 1875;`
  line
  line `^4[(ee) "orchard" means a compact area of land, having fruit bearing trees grown thereon in such`
  line `number that they preclude or when fully grown, would preclude, a substantial part of such land from`
  line `being used for any agricultural purpose, but does not include any land, being a banana or guava`
  line `garden or vine yard;`
  line
  line `(eee) "person" includes a company, family, association or other body of individuals, whether`
  line `incorporated or not, and any institution capable of holding property;]`
  line
  line `(f) "person under disability" means--`
  line
  line `(i) a widow;`
  line
  line `(ii) a minor;`
  line
  line `(iii) a woman unmarried or, if married, divorced or judicially separated from her husband or`
  line `whose husband is a person falling under sub-clause (iv) or sub-clause (v);`
  line
  line `(iv) a member of the Armed Forces of the Union;`
  line
  line `(v) a person incapable of cultivating land by reason of some physical or mental disability;`
  line
  line `(g) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(h) the words and expressions "Asami", "Bhumidhar", "Deputy Commissioner", "Gaon`
  line `Panchayat", "improvement", "land" ^5*** and "village" shall have the meanings respectively assigned`
  line `to them in the Delhi Land Reforms Act, 1954 (Delhi Act 8 1954).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (aa) by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for clause (d) (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `5. The words ', "standard acre" ' omitted by Act 15 of 1976, s. 3 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (40210)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Ceiling on holding.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 4, ibid., for section 3 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40210&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[3. Ceiling on holding.-- (1) Subject to the provisions of this section, on and from the`
  line `commencement of the Delhi Land Holdings (Ceiling) Amendment Act, 1976, no person either by himself`
  line `or, if he has a family, together with any other member of his family (hereinafter referred to as the person`
  line `representing the family) shall, whether as a Bhumidhar or an Asami or partly in one capacity and partly in`
  line `another, be entitled to hold land in excess of--`
  line
  line `(a) (i) 7.25 hectares, in the case of land which is assured of irrigation from a private source of`
  line `irrigation and is capable of yielding at least two crops in a year; or`
  line
  line `(ii) 5.8 hectares, in the case of land which is assured of irrigation from a Government source of`
  line `irrigation and is capable of yielding at least two crops in a year; or`
  line
  line `(b) (i) 10.9 hectares, in the case of land which is assured of irrigation from a private source of`
  line `irrigation and is capable of yielding at least one crop in a year; or`
  line
  line `(ii) 8.7 hectares, in the case of land which is assured of irrigation from a Government source of`
  line `irrigation and is capable of yielding at least one crop in a year; or`
  line
  line `(c) 21.8 hectares, in the case of any other land, including an orchard.`
  line
  line `(2) Where a person holds land falling under more than one category specified in sub-section (1), then,`
  line `the land held by him shall be converted into land falling under category (c) and for the purpose of such`
  line `conversion one hectare of land falling under category (a) (i) shall be treated as equal to 3 hectares of land`
  line `falling under category (c), one hectare of land falling under category (a) (ii) shall be treated as equal to`
  line `3.75 hectares of land falling under category (c), one hectare of land falling under category (b) (i) shall be`
  line `treated as equal to 2 hectares of land falling under category (c) and one hectare of land falling under`
  line `category (b) (ii) shall be treated as equal to 2.5 hectares of land falling under category (c); and the extent`
  line `of the land so converted together with the extent of the land, if any falling under category (c) held by such`
  line `person shall not exceed 21.8 hectares.`
  line
  line `(3) For the purposes of this section, land which is assured of irrigation from a Government source of`
  line `irrigation means any land which is irrigated, or is capable of being irrigated, from such source.`
  line
  line `(4) If any question whether any land is capable of yielding only one crop or more than one crop in a`
  line `year arises, such question shall be decided by such authority and in such manner as may be prescribed and`
  line `the decision of such authority thereon shall be final.`
  line
  line `(5) Where the number of members of the family of a person exceeds five, he shall he entitled to hold`
  line `land in excess of the ceiling limit to the extent of one-fifth of the ceiling limit for each member in excess`
  line `of five; so, however, as not to exceed twice the ceiling limit in the aggregate.`
  line
  line `(6) where a person is a member of a family the land held by such person together with the land held`
  line `by every other member of the family, whether individually or jointly, shall be taken into account in`
  line `determining the ceiling limit.`
  line
  line `(7) A person representing a family shall also be entitled to hold land not exceeding the ceiling limit`
  line `for each of his major sons, if any:`
  line
  line `Provided that the land, if any, held by such major son or, if he has a family, by any other member of`
  line `his family shall be taken into account in determining the ceiling limit for the purposes of this sub-section.`
  line
  line `(8) Where a family holds land in excess of the ceiling limit and such land includes land held by the`
  line `wife or the husband, then, the share of the wife or the husband, as the case may he, in the land that may be`
  line `held by the family within the ceiling limit shall be in the same proportion as it was in the total extent of`
  line `the land held by the family.`
  line
  line `(9) Where a person is a member of a registered co-operative farming society his share in the land held`
  line `by such society shall be taken into account in calculating the ceiling limit in relation to such person.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (40211)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Submission of returns.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 5, for certain words (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40211&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `Every person representing a family ^1[who on the appointed day or at any`
  line `time thereafter held or holds,] land in excess of the ceiling limit shall submit to the competent authority,`
  line `in such form and within such time as may be prescribed, a return giving the particulars of all land held by`
  line `him and indicating therein the parcels of land, not exceeding the ceiling limit, which he desires to retain:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a joint holding, all co-sharers may submit the return jointly indicating the`
  line `parcels of land, not exceeding the aggregate of their individual ceiling limits, which they desire to retain.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In the case of a person under disability, the return shall be furnished by his guardian or`
  line `authorised agent, as the case may be.`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (40212)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Collection of information through other agency.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40212&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `If any person, who under section 4 is required`
  line `to submit a return, fails to do so in accordance with the provisions of that section, the competent authority`
  line `shall collect the necessary information through such agency as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (40213)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Procedure for determination of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 6, ibid., for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40213&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) On receipt of any return under section 4 or`
  line `information under section 5 or otherwise, the competent authority shell, after giving the persons affected`
  line `an opportunity of being heard, hold an inquiry in such manner as may be prescribed, and having regard to`
  line `the provisions of section 7 and section 8 or of any rules that may be made in this behalf, it shall`
  line determine--
  line
  line `(a) the total area of land held by each person representing the family;`
  line
  line `(b) the specific parcels of land which he may retain;`
  line
  line `(c) the land held by him in excess of the ceiling limit;`
  line
  line `(d) whether such excess land is held by him as a Bhumidhar or as an Asami;`
  line
  line `(e) the excess land in respect of which Bhumidhari rights may be acquired by an Asami;`
  line
  line `(f) the excess land which may be restored to a Bhumidhar;`
  line
  line `(g) the excess land which shall vest in the Government; and`
  line
  line `(h) such other matters as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) For the purpose of determining the excess land under this section any land transferred by sale,`
  line `gift or otherwise (other than a bona fide sale under a registered deed for valuable consideration) at any`
  line `time during the period between the appointed day and the commencement of the Delhi Land Holdings (Ceiling) Amendment Act, 1976, shall, notwithstanding such transfer, be deemed to be held by the`
  line `transferor and the burden of proving the transfer by sale as bona fide shall be on the transferor.`
  line
  line `(3) The competent authority shall prepare a list in the prescribed form containing the particulars`
  line `determined by him under sub-section (1) and shall cause every such list to be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (40214)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Selection of excess land in cases of certain transfers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 7, for section 7 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40214&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[7. Selection of excess land in cases of certain transfers.-- (1) Where any person transfers any`
  line `land by sale, gift or otherwise (other than a bona fide sale under a registered deed for valuable`
  line `consideration) at any time during the period referred to in sub-section (2) of section 6, the excess land in`
  line `relation to such person shall be selected from out of the land held by him after such transfer and in case`
  line `the entire excess land cannot be so selected, the balance, or, where no land is held by him after the`
  line `transfer, the entire excess land, shall be selected out of the land held by the transferee:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such person has transferred his land to more than one person, the balance or the`
  line `entire excess land, as the case may be, shall be selected out of the land held by each of the transferees in`
  line `the same proportion as the area of the land transferred to him bears to the total area of the land transferred`
  line `to all the transferees.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any excess land is selected out of the land transferred, the transfer of such land shall be`
  line void.]
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (40215)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 8
  title `Abatement of certain suits.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 7, for section 7 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40215&sectionno=7A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[7A. Abatement of certain suits.-- Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law, every suit`
  line `for the specific performance of a contract for the transfer of land, instituted after the appointed day and`
  line `before the commencement of the Delhi Land Holdings (Ceiling) Amendment Act, 1976 shall abate and no`
  line `suit for the specific performance of any such contract entered into before such commencement shall be`
  line maintainable.]
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (40216)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 9
  title `Excess land to vest in Government.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40216&sectionno=8&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where any excess land of a Bhumidhar is in his actual`
  line `possession, the excess land shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any excess land of a Bhumidhar is in the possession of a person holding the same as an`
  line `Asami and the excess land together with any other land held by such person exceeds his ceiling limit, the`
  line `land in excess of the ceiling limit shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(3) Where any excess land of a Bhumidhar is in the possession of a person holding the same as an`
  line `Asami and such person is allowed to retain the excess land or a part thereof as being within his ceiling`
  line `limit, that parson shall acquire Bhumidhari rights in respect of such excess land or part thereof on`
  line `payment of compensation as hereinafter provided, but if that person refuses to pay such compensation, the`
  line `excess land or part thereof shall vest in the Government.`
  line
  line `(4) Where there is any excess land of an Asami, the excess land shall vest in the Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that in any case where the excess land or any part thereof held by a Bhumidhar together`
  line `with any other land held by such person does not exceed the ceiling limit, the excess land or such part`
  line `thereof as does not exceed the ceiling limit shall be restored to the Bhumidhar on an application made by`
  line `him in this behalf to the competent authority within such time as may be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (40217)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 10
  title `Publication of the final list and consequences thereof.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40217&sectionno=9&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) Any person aggrieved by an entry in`
  line `the list published under sub-section (3) of section 6 may, within thirty days from the date of publication`
  line `thereof in the Official Gazette, file objections thereto before the Deputy Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Deputy Commissioner may entertain the objection after the expiry of the said period`
  line `of thirty days, if he is satisfied that the objector was prevented by sufficient cause from filing the`
  line `objection in time.`
  line
  line `(2) The Deputy Commissioner or any other officer authorised in this behalf by the Chief`
  line `Commissioner may, after considering the objections and after giving the objector or his representatives an`
  line `opportunity of being heard in the matter, approve or modify the list`
  line
  line `(3) The list as approved or modified under sub-section (2) shall then be published in the Official`
  line `Gazette and also in such other manner as may be prescribed and, subject to the provisions of this Act, the`
  line `list shall be final.`
  line
  line `(4) With effect from the date of the publication of the list in the Official Gazette under`
  line `sub-section (3), the excess land shall stand transferred to, and vest in, the Government free of all`
  line `encumbrances or, as the case may be, the excess land shall stand restored to the Bhumidhar or the`
  line `Bhumidhari rights in respect of the excess land shall stand transferred to the Asami free of all`
  line encumbrances.
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (40218)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 11
  title Compensation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40218&sectionno=10&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1) Where any excess land of a Bhumidhar vests in the Government, there`
  line `shall be paid by the Government to the Bhumidhar an amount calculated at the rates specified in the Table`
  line `below, namely:--`
  line
  line `THE TABLE`
  line
  line `Rates per hectare in rupees`
  line
  line `Class of land For the first 3`
  line
  line hectares
  line `For the next 3`
  line hectares
  line `For the`
  line `remaining area`
  line
  line `(a) Land under assured irrigation and capable of`
  line `yielding at least two crops in a year`
  line `5,000 4,400 4,000`
  line
  line `(b) Land under assured irrigation and capable of`
  line `yielding at least one crop in a year`
  line `2,500 2,200 2,000`
  line
  line `(c) Any other land (including an orchard) 1,250 1,100 1,000`
  line
  line `Provided that where such excess land or any part thereof is in the possession of an Asami, the`
  line `amount payable in respect of the land shall be apportioned between the Bhumidhar and the Asami in such`
  line `proportion as may be determined by the competent authority in the prescribed manner, having regard to`
  line `their respective shares in the net income from such land to be determined by the competent authority in`
  line `the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the amount payable in respect of any excess land under sub-section (1), there shall`
  line `also be paid an amount in respect of any structure or building, including wells, tube-wells and`
  line `embankments constructed on such excess land and such amount shall be fifty per cent. of the market`
  line `value of such structure or building and shall be paid to the person who has constructed the structure or`
  line building.]
  line
  line `(3) Where any excess land in respect of which ^2[an amount] is payable is subject to any mortgage or`
  line `other encumbrance, the amount due under the mortgage or other encumbrance in respect of such excess`
  line `land, or where a transfer in respect of excess land is void by virtue of ^3[sub-section (2) of section 7], the consideration money paid by the transferee in respect of such excess land, shall be a charge on the`
  line `^4[amount] payable in respect of the excess land to the person who has created the mortgage or`
  line `encumbrance or, as the case may be, to the transferor.`
  line
  line `(4) Where an Asami acquires Bhumidhari rights in respect of any excess land, ^5[`
  line `the amount] payable`
  line `by him in respect of that land shall be equal to the amount which the Bhumidhar would have been paid`
  line `^6*** under the proviso to sub-section (1) or sub-section (2), if the land had vested in the Government; and`
  line `the amount shall, in the first instance, be paid to the Bhumidhar by the Government and shall be`
  line `recovered from the Asami in such manner as may be prescribed`
  line
  line `(5) Where any excess land of a religious or charitable institution vests in the Government such`
  line `institution shall, in lieu of ^4[the amount] payable under sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) be paid an`
  line `annuity equal to the net annual income of the excess land and such net annual income shall be determined`
  line `by the competent authority in the prescribed manner.`
  line
  line `(6) The competent authority shall, after holding an inquiry in the prescribed manner, make an order`
  line `determining the amount ^7*** payable to any person under this section.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 8, for sub-sections (1) and (2) (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `2. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `3. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for sub-section (4) of section 7 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `4. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 8, for "compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `5. Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for "the compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `6. The words "as compensation" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line `7. The words "of compensation" omitted by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (40219)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 12
  title `Manner of payment of amount.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 9, ibid., for "compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40219&sectionno=11&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) The ^1[amount] payable under section 10 shall be due on`
  line `the date of the publication of the list in the Official Gazette under sub-section (3) of section 9 and may be`
  line `paid in cash, in a lump sum or in instalments or in bonds.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the ^1[amount] is payable in bonds, the bonds may be made not transferable or transferable`
  line `by endorsement or in any other manner but all such bonds shall be redeemed within such period, not`
  line `exceeding ten years from the dare of issue, as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Where there is any delay in the payment of ^1[amount] or where the ^1[amount] is paid either in`
  line `instalments or in bonds, it shall carry interest at the rate of two and a half per cent. per annum from the`
  line `date on which it falls due.`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (40220)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 13
  title `Limit of future acquisition of land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40220&sectionno=12&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `No person representing a family shall acquire in any`
  line `manner whatsoever whether by transfer, exchange, lease, agreement or succession any land where such`
  line `acquisition has the effect of making the total area of the land held by him exceed the ceiling limit; and any`
  line `such land in excess of the ceiling limit shall, subject to the provisions of the Delhi Land Reforms Act,`
  line `1954 (Delhi Act 8 of 1954), be treated as excess land of the transferee and the provisions of sections 6 to`
  line `11 shall, as far as may be, apply to such excess land.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (40221)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 14
  title `Excess land not to be surrendered in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40221&sectionno=13&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Where a person representing a family`
  line `holds land not exceeding the ceiling limit, but subsequently the land held exceeds the ceiling limit, then,`
  line `notwithstanding anything contained in this Chapter, such person shall not be required to surrender any`
  line `part of the land on the ground that it is excess land, if such excess is due to any improvements effected in`
  line `the land by the efforts of the family or to a decrease in the number of its members.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (40222)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 15
  title `Power of Deputy Commissioner to take possession of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40222&sectionno=14&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `After the publication of`
  line `the list of excess land under sub-section (3) of section 9, and after demarcation in the prescribed manner`
  line `of such land where necessary, the Deputy Commissioner may take possession of any excess land and may`
  line `use or cause to be used such force as may be necessary for the purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (40223)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 16
  title `Reservation of land for certain purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40223&sectionno=15&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `The Chief Commissioner may reserve any excess`
  line `land vesting in the Government under the provisions of this Act for the benefit of the village community`
  line `or for any work of public utility or for such other purposes as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where such land is not being used for the aforesaid purposes, it may be used by the`
  line `Gaon Panchayat for such purposes as the Chief Commissioner may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (40224)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 17
  title `Allotment of excess land.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 10, for "to such persons" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40224&sectionno=16&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any rules that may be made in this behalf, the Chief`
  line `Commissioner or any officer authorised by him may allot any excess land vesting in the Government`
  line `(other than land reserved under section 15) ^1[to such persons (preference being given to landless`
  line `agricultural labourers particularly those belonging to the Scheduled Castes or the Scheduled Tribes)] and`
  line `on such terms and conditions as he thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (40225)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 18
  title `Act to override contract and other laws.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40225&sectionno=17&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `Save as otherwise expressly provided, the provisions`
  line `of this Act shall have effect notwithstanding anything to the contrary contained in any other law, custom`
  line `or usage or agreement or decree or order of a court.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (40226)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 19
  title `Mode of recovery of any amount due under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40226&sectionno=18&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `Any sum payable to the Government`
  line `under the provisions of this Act may be recovered in the same manner as an arrear of land revenue.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (40227)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 20
  title Appeal.
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40227&sectionno=19&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `Any person aggrieved by an order made by the competent authority under section 10,`
  line `may, within a period of thirty days from the date of the order, prefer an appeal to the Deputy`
  line `Commissioner:`
  line
  line `Provided that the Deputy Commissioner may entertain the appeal after the expiry of the said period, if`
  line `he is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by sufficient cause from preferring the appeal in time.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (40228)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 21
  title Revision.
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40228&sectionno=20&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, on an application for revision made to him or`
  line `otherwise, call for the record of any proceeding pending before, or disposed of by, the competent`
  line `authority or the Deputy Commissioner or any officer authorised by the Chief Commissioner under`
  line `sub-section (2) of section 9.`
  line
  line `(2) No order varying the decision of the competent authority or the Deputy Commissioner or revising`
  line `the list published under section 9 which prejudicially affects any person shall be made without giving him`
  line `an opportunity of being heard.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (40229)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power of officers while holding inquiries, etc., under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40229&sectionno=21&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `Any officer or authority while`
  line `holding an inquiry or hearing an appeal or exercising powers of revision under this Act shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), when`
  line `trying a suit, in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him on oath;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of documents and material objects;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavit; and`
  line
  line `(d) such other matters as may be prescribed`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (40230)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 23
  title `Entry upon land for purposes of survey, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40230&sectionno=22&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `Subject to any conditions and restrictions that`
  line `may be prescribed, any officer entrusted with the performance of any duty under this Act may, in the`
  line `discharge of such duty, enter upon and survey and take measurement of any land and do all other acts`
  line `necessary for carrying out his duties under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (40231)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 24
  title `Offences and penalties.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 11, for "shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40231&sectionno=23&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `(1) Whoever being bound to submit a return under section 4 fails`
  line `without reasonable cause to do so, within the prescribed time, or submits a return which he knows or has`
  line `reason to believe to be false, ^1[shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to six`
  line `months and with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever contravenes any lawful order made under this Act or otherwise obstructs any person`
  line `from lawfully taking possession of any land shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (40232)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 25
  title `Finality of orders and bar of jurisdiction.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40232&sectionno=24&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to the provisions of this Act, every`
  line `order made under this Act shall be final.`
  line
  line `(2) No civil court shall have jurisdiction to entertain any suit or proceeding in so far as it relates to`
  line `any matter which the competent authority or the Deputy Commissioner is empowered by or under this`
  line `Act to decide.`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (40233)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 26
  title `Protection of action taken under the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40233&sectionno=25&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against`
  line `the Government or any authority or officer in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended`
  line `to be done in pursuance of this Act or any rules or orders made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (40234)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 27
  title Omitted.
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40234&sectionno=26&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `[Power to exempt, etc.] Omitted by the Delhi Land Holdings (Ceiling) Amendment Act,`
  line `(15 of 1976), s. 12 (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (40235)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 28
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40235&sectionno=27&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Chief Commissioner may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the form in which and the period within which a return under section 4 may be submitted;`
  line
  line `(b) the agency through which information under section 5 may be collected;`
  line
  line `(c) the manner of holding inquiries under this Act;`
  line
  line `(d) the matters which may be determined by the compelent authority under sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 6 and the manner of determination of excess land under the Act;`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which a list under sub-section (3) of section 6 or sub-section (3) of section 9 may`
  line `be prepared and the manner of publication of such list;`
  line
  line `(f) the period within which an application for restoration of excess land of an Asami may be made`
  line `by the Bhumidhar;`
  line
  line `(g) the manner of apportionment of ^1[amount] between the Bhumidhar and the Asami in respect`
  line `of any excess land in the possession of the Asami;`
  line
  line `(h) the manner of determination of the net annual income of any excess land for the purposes of`
  line `payment of ^1[amount];`
  line
  line `(i) the manner of assessment of market value of structures and buildings and the value of trees for`
  line `the purpose of payment of ^1[amount];`
  line
  line `(j) the number of instalments in which ^1[any amount] under this Act may be paid or recovered;`
  line `and the period within which bonds may be redeemed;`
  line
  line `(k) the manner of demarcation of excess land;`
  line
  line `(l) the purposes for which land may be reserved under section 15;`
  line
  line `(m) the categories of persons to whom excess land may be allotted and the terms and conditions`
  line `on which such allotment may be made;`
  line
  line `(n) the powers of a civil court which may be vested in any officer or authority holding an inquiry;`
  line
  line `(o) the conditions and restrictions subject to which an officer may enter upon any land for the`
  line `purpose of survey and taking measurement;`
  line
  line `(p) the levy of fees in respect of any matter under this Act;`
  line
  line `(q) any other matter which has to be, or may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days ^2[which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid], both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be, so however that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 15 of 1976, s. 13, for "compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by s. 13, ibid., for "compensation" (w.e.f. 8-12-1975).`
obj_root_law_sections_28:
  sectionId (40236)
  sectionNo (28)
  orderNo 29
  title Repealed.
  content obj_root_law_sections_28_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468&sectionId=40236&sectionno=28&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00002_196024_1517807319468
obj_root_law_sections_28_content:
  string
  line `[Amendment of the Delhi Land Reforms Act, 1954.] Rep. by the Repealing and Amending Act,`
  line `1964 (52 of 1964), s. 2 and the First Schedule (w.e.f. 29-12-1964).`
obj_root_law_sections_28_footnotes:
  string
  line
